AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - RUSSIA: (NIZHEGOROD) SPREAD, OIE
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 18 Feb 2011
Source: Rosselkhoznadzor (Federal Service for Veterinary and
Phytosanitary Surveillance) News [edited]
<http://fsvps.ru/fsvps/news/2891.html?_language=en>


ASF outbreak in the Nizhny Novgorod Oblast [region]
---------------------------------------------------
A new outbreak of African swine fever (ASF) was reported out of the
permanently affected area (the Southern Federal District and the North
Caucasian Federal District) in the Nizhny Novgorod [Nizhegorod]
Oblast. The outbreak was reported at 7:45 on 18 Feb 2011 in [a
backyard in] the city of Dzershinsk.

Preliminary diagnosis was made in the regional veterinary laboratory
on the same day and some hours later it was confirmed by the National
Reference Laboratory for ASF -- All-Russia Research Institute of
Virology and Microbiology (Pokrov, Vladimir Oblast).

Commission attached to the governor of the Nizhny Novgorod Oblast held
a meeting to determine urgent measures aimed at eradication of ASF in
accordance with the contingency plan approved by the regulation of the
local government.

It is assumed that the virus was introduced into the backyard with
catering wastes from a military unit located nearby. The outbreak in
the Nizhny Novgorod Oblast and the recent outbreak in St. Petersburg
are like 2 peas in a pod.

Commission on emergency situations held a meeting in Dzershinsk where
an action plan was developed to eradicate the ASF outbreak.

Measures were taken to contain the outbreak in the affected area. The
pigs from the backyard were destroyed. Measures are being prepared to
destroy the dead animals and materials contaminated with the virus.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
Castleview Pedigree English Longhorns
Gut Laach
52385 Nideggen
Germany
<http://www.cvlonghorns.de>
